**Problem:** `submit_transaction()` in the blockchain RPC called `get_chain_id("")` which returned `""` (empty string) instead of the default chain ID. The `get_chain_id()` function only falls back to `settings.chain_id` when the argument is `None`, not when it's an empty string. This caused every transaction submission to fail with `transaction.chain_id is required`.

**Fix:** Changed `get_chain_id("")` to `get_chain_id(None)`.

